<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 17 at 10:20PM EST  by NWS Boston</headline>
<description>...ICY SPOTS ON ROADWAYS INTO EARLY TUESDAY MORNING...
Any remaining standing water and slush will freeze solid
overnight. This may result in icy spots developing on roadways as
temperatures will be dropping into the 20s overnight. This is
particularly true in areas that received a brief burst of snow
earlier this evening; which may cover icy patches beneath it.
Motorists are urged to drive with caution overnight into early
Tuesday morning.</description>
